    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The original name was Newton Colony, later called Oakland the Beautiful, before becoming Oaklyn in 1894 to avoid confusion.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14,
        23,
        24
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oaklyn%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Oaklyn was officially incorporated as a borough on March 13, 1905, separating from Haddon Township.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        25
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oaklyn%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The Black Horse Pike, a historic trail from Delaware River to Egg Harbor, runs through Oaklyn and was once a Native American path.",
